5 A BILL
6 TO BE ENTITLED
7 AN ACT
8
9 Relating to motor vehicle licenses and registration; to
10 amend Sections 32-6-62 and 32-6-64, Code of Alabama 1975, to
11 extend the minimum validity period of motor vehicle license
12 plate designs from five years to 10 years.
13 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF ALABAMA:
14 Section 1. Sections 32-6-62 and 32-6-64, Code of
15 Alabama 1975, are amended to read as follows:
16 "§32-6-62
17 (a) Subject to subsection (b), all motor vehicle
18 license plate designs shall be valid for not less than five10
19 years. The Commissioner of Revenue, with the approval of the
20 License Plates Legislative Oversight Committee established by
21 Section 32-6-67, may authorize a license plate design to be
22 valid for more than five10 years.
23 (b) Subsection (a) shall not affect any law which
24 designates a license plate design to be permanent."
25 "§32-6-64
26 (a)(1) The design of license plates, including all
27 emblems, slogans, symbols, or characters appearing on the
28 plates, shall be, by rule, as adopted by the Commissioner of
Page 1

plates, shall be, by rule, as adopted by the Commissioner of
